# Copy to apps/mobile/.env and fill in your backend's reachable address.
# Unlike env/server.env and env/web.env, this can't be read directly from
# env/ — Expo's env loading (@expo/env) always reads apps/mobile/.env, and it
# runs before a dynamic app.config.js/.ts even gets evaluated, so redirecting
# it via app.config.ts doesn't work either (verified: process.env is already
# populated from apps/mobile/.env by the time app.config.ts's own code runs,
# and @expo/env never overwrites an already-set var). So this file is only
# the canonical template; the actual working file has to stay at apps/mobile/.env.
#
# - iOS Simulator / Android Emulator: http://localhost:3000 works.
# - Expo Go on a physical device: the phone can't reach "localhost" (that's
#   the phone itself) — use your machine's LAN IP instead, e.g.
#   http://192.168.1.77:3000. Find it with `ipconfig getifaddr en0` (macOS Wi-Fi).
# - Must be prefixed EXPO_PUBLIC_ to be readable from app code (Expo inlines
#   only EXPO_PUBLIC_* vars into the client bundle).
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
